  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will gather information on the effectiveness and safety of a treatment program for
      small cell lung cancer (SCLC) that uses an FDA approved chemotherapy combination, radiation
      therapy, and an oral investigational drug that may enhance the effects of radiation therapy.
      Study patients will receive two additional courses of the standard chemotherapy combination
      after completing radiation therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
